docs.abstract: Nike has often tried to capitalize on controversy. Will marketing featuring Colin Kaepernick pay off?
docs.snippet: Nike has often tried to capitalize on controversy. Will marketing featuring Colin Kaepernick pay off?
docs.lead_paragraph: Nike has long relied on controversy in marketing an image of edgy youthfulness. The company had Charles Barkley declare that he was not a role model and Tiger Woods remind people that some country clubs would turn him away because of his skin color. It dressed the tennis player Andre Agassi in jean shorts.

headline.main: Nike Returns to Familiar Strategy With Kaepernick Ad Campaign
headline.print_headline: Take a Big Risk  On an Activist?  Nike Just Did It

docs.abstract: Patrick Mahomes looks to extend a record-setting start; the Packers hope to rebound in Washington; and Los Angeles teams play each other for the first time since 1994.
docs.snippet: Patrick Mahomes looks to extend a record-setting start; the Packers hope to rebound in Washington; and Los Angeles teams play each other for the first time since 1994.
docs.lead_paragraph: People tend to like touchdowns and close games, so this N.F.L. season has truly delivered. The N.F.L. has produced the most touchdowns, and the second most overall points, through two weeks of any season in its history, and according to the league, 25 of the 32 games have been within one score at some point in fourth quarter. For those who like to factor in drama, there have even been nine fourth-quarter comebacks.

headline.main: N.F.L. Week 3: Our Picks Against the Spread
headline.print_headline: The Point of the Season Is Points

docs.abstract: “Soul of a Nation: Art in the Age of Black Power” at the Brooklyn Museum shows how black artists were galvanized during a time of social and political unrest.
docs.snippet: “Soul of a Nation: Art in the Age of Black Power” at the Brooklyn Museum shows how black artists were galvanized during a time of social and political unrest.
docs.lead_paragraph: It will be a happy day when racial harmony rules in this land. But that day’s not coming any time soon. Who could have guessed in the 1960s, when civil rights became law, that a new century would bring white supremacy tiki torching out of the closet and turn the idea that black lives matter, so beyond obvious, into a desperate battle cry?

headline.main: Radiant and Radical: 20 Years of Defining the Soul of Black Art
